d nature at the Tyura Tam Missile Test Range (TTMTR) on 16 May 1959. The countdown operation began with \"X-8\" hours at 0855 EDST and reached \"X-4\" at 1100 EDST. The operation was canceled shortly thereafter, possibly because of communications difficulties between the range elements.\n\nOne possibly significant variation from all previous TTMTR launchings was noted during this operation; the time intervals between the X-8 hour announcement and subsequent announcements down to X-4 were considerably shortened, being respectively 16, 16, 36, and 57 minutes. While no firm reason for this time compression can currently be given, it is possible that this may presage for selected operations at TTMTR a considerable decrease in real time consumed in the countdown procedure", "token_count": 129, "token_end_0based": 140, "token_start_0based": 12, "token_text": "ussr an attempt was made to launch a vehicle of undetermined nature at the tyura tam missile test range ttmtr on 16 may 1959 the countdown operation began with x-8 hours at 0855 edst and reached x-4 at 1100 edst the operation was canceled shortly thereafter possibly because of communications difficulties between the range elements one possibly significant variation from all previous ttmtr launchings was noted during this operation the time intervals between the x-8 hour announcement and subsequent announcements down to x-4 were considerably shortened being respectively 16 16 36 and 57 minutes while no firm reason for this time compression can currently be given it is possible that this may presage for selected operations at ttmtr a considerable decrease in real time consumed in the countdown procedure", "unred_source_page": 4}
